    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-11-01</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-11-30T16:57:50Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Mortgage Disclosure Enhancement Act of 2007 - Amends the Truth In Lending Act to require additional mortgage loan disclosures by a creditor to a consumer, including: (1) ) the percentage of the loan, as compared to the appraised value of the property; (2) the term of the loan; (3) the monthly income of the borrower, as relied upon in making the loan; (4) the annual percentage rate of interest for loans that are fixed, and for loans that are variable; (5) prepayment fees; and (6) balloon payments.</p> <p>Amends the Real Estate Settlement Procedures Act of 1974 to conform with this Act.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
